1 A JOINT RESOLUTION designating the Mae Street Kidd Memorial Highway in
2 Jefferson County.
3 WHEREAS, Minnie Mae Jones, better known as Mae Street Kidd, was born on
4 February 8, 1904, in Millersburg, Kentucky; and
5 WHEREAS, Mae Street Kidd grew up attending segregated schools into her high
6 school years, and attended the Lincoln Institute, a black boarding academy near
7 Shelbyville, Kentucky, to continue her education; and
8 WHEREAS, Mae Street Kidd began a career as a business woman working for
9 Mammoth Life and Accident Insurance Company in Louisville, Kentucky; and
10 WHEREAS, Mae Street Kidd met her first husband, Horace Leon Street, in
11 Louisville and they were married for 12 years, until his untimely death in 1942; and
12 WHEREAS, Mae Street Kidd served with the Red Cross in England during World
13 War II, and this is also where she met her second husband, James Meredith Kidd III; and
14 WHEREAS, Mae Street Kidd was elected to represent Louisville's District 41 in
15 Kentucky's House of Representatives in 1968, and she remained in the position until
16 1984; and
17 WHEREAS, Mae Street Kidd sponsored Kentucky's ratification of the Thirteenth,
18 Fourteenth, and Fifteenth Amendments to the United States Constitution in 1976; and
19 WHEREAS, Mae Street Kidd was instrumental in sponsoring the bill that created
20 the Kentucky Housing Corporation in 1972 that provides open and low-income housing;
21 and
22 WHEREAS, Mae Street Kidd passed away on October 20, 1999, and her legacy and
23 career in the Kentucky General Assembly is deserving of tangible representation;
24 NOW, THEREFORE,
25 Be it resolved by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
